---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="Financial Disclaimer | MoneyJuan"
	description="MoneyJuan financial disclaimer and limitations of general educational content."
>
	<div class="container page-content">
		<h1 class="page-title">Financial Disclaimer</h1>
		<p class="last-updated"><strong>Last Updated: February 9, 2026</strong></p>

		<div class="content-wrapper">
			<section class="policy-section">
				<h2>Not Professional Financial Advice</h2>
				<p>
					MoneyJuan provides general financial information and education for Filipinos. We are not licensed financial advisors, investment professionals, accountants, lawyers, or tax experts.
				</p>
				<p>
					Nothing on this website constitutes professional financial, investment, legal, or tax advice. Our content should not be relied upon as the sole basis for any financial decision.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section class="policy-section">
				<h2>Educational Content Only</h2>
				<p>Our articles, guides, comparisons, and reviews are educational resources designed to help you:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Understand financial concepts</li>
					<li>Learn about available financial products</li>
					<li>Compare options in the Philippine market</li>
					<li>Make more informed financial decisions</li>
				</ul>
				<p>
					This information is general in nature and does not consider your individual circumstances, financial situation, needs, or objectives.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section class="policy-section">
				<h2>Consult Licensed Professionals</h2>
				<p>Before making significant financial decisions, consult with licensed professionals:</p>
				<ul>
					<li><strong>Financial Planning:</strong> Consult a licensed financial advisor or planner</li>
					<li><strong>Investments:</strong> Consult a licensed investment advisor or broker</li>
					<li><strong>Taxes:</strong> Consult a licensed accountant or tax professional</li>
					<li><strong>Legal Matters:</strong> Consult a licensed attorney</li>
					<li><strong>Insurance:</strong> Consult a licensed insurance agent or broker</li>
				</ul>
				<p>
					Professional advice considers your specific situation, which we cannot do through general website content.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section class="policy-section">
				<h2>Verify All Information</h2>
				<p>
					Interest rates, fees, terms, and policies change frequently. Financial institutions update their products without notice. While we strive for accuracy:
				</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Always verify current rates and terms directly with the financial institution</li>
					<li>Read all product disclosures and fine print before signing up</li>
					<li>Confirm eligibility requirements before applying</li>
					<li>Check for recent policy changes that may affect you</li>
				</ul>
				<p>Do not rely solely on our content for time-sensitive financial decisions.</p>
			</section>

			<section class="policy-section">
				<h2>No Guaranteed Results</h2>
				<p>Financial outcomes depend on numerous factors beyond our control or knowledge:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Your personal financial situation and history</li>
					<li>Market conditions and economic changes</li>
					<li>Individual discipline and behavior</li>
					<li>Timing and execution of strategies</li>
					<li>Unforeseen circumstances and emergencies</li>
				</ul>
				<p>We make no guarantees about results you may achieve. Past performance does not guarantee future results.</p>
			</section>

			<section class="policy-section">
				<h2>Investment Risk Disclosure</h2>
				<p>All investments carry risk, including potential loss of principal. Content discussing investments or investment strategies:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Is not a recommendation to buy or sell any security</li>
					<li>Does not consider your risk tolerance or investment timeline</li>
					<li>Cannot predict future market performance</li>
					<li>Does not guarantee any return or outcome</li>
				</ul>
				<p>Invest only what you can afford to lose. Understand the risks before investing.</p>
			</section>

			<section class="policy-section">
				<h2>Banking and Financial Products</h2>
				<p>Information about banks, digital banks, loans, credit cards, and other financial products:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Represents our understanding based on publicly available information</li>
					<li>May not reflect the most current terms and conditions</li>
					<li>Does not account for your creditworthiness or eligibility</li>
					<li>Is not an endorsement or recommendation of any specific product</li>
				</ul>
				<p>Terms and availability vary by individual. You may not qualify for advertised rates or products.</p>
			</section>

			<section class="policy-section">
				<h2>Affiliate Compensation Disclosure</h2>
				<p>
					MoneyJuan may earn affiliate commissions when you sign up for products or services through our links. This compensation:
				</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Does not influence our factual reporting of rates, fees, or features</li>
					<li>Does not change the price you pay</li>
					<li>Does not create any obligation or endorsement</li>
					<li>Is disclosed where applicable</li>
				</ul>
				<p>
					We only partner with legitimate financial institutions and products. However, affiliate relationships exist and may influence which products we choose to write about.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section class="policy-section">
				<h2>No Liability for Financial Decisions</h2>
				<p>MoneyJuan and its operators are not liable for:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Financial losses from decisions based on our content</li>
					<li>Losses from outdated or incorrect information</li>
					<li>Results that differ from examples or scenarios presented</li>
					<li>Actions taken by third-party financial institutions</li>
					<li>Changes to products, rates, or terms after publication</li>
				</ul>
				<p>You assume full responsibility for your financial decisions and their outcomes.</p>
			</section>

			<section class="policy-section">
				<h2>Philippine Market Focus</h2>
				<p>
					Our content focuses on the Philippine financial market and is intended for Filipino residents. Financial products, regulations, and tax implications differ by country. Information may not apply to:
				</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Overseas Filipino Workers (OFWs) subject to foreign tax laws</li>
					<li>Non-residents or foreign nationals</li>
					<li>International investment or banking situations</li>
					<li>Cross-border financial transactions</li>
				</ul>
				<p>
					Consult professionals familiar with your jurisdiction if you have international financial considerations.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section class="policy-section">
				<h2>No Personal Relationship</h2>
				<p>Using MoneyJuan does not create any:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Advisory or fiduciary relationship</li>
					<li>Client or professional relationship</li>
					<li>Duty of care or ongoing obligation to you</li>
					<li>Responsibility for monitoring your financial situation</li>
				</ul>
			</section>

			<section class="policy-section">
				<h2>Third-Party Information</h2>
				<p>We reference information from banks, government agencies, and other third parties. We are not responsible for:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Accuracy of third-party information</li>
					<li>Changes made by third parties after our publication</li>
					<li>Third-party errors or omissions</li>
					<li>Actions or policies of third-party institutions</li>
				</ul>
			</section>

			<section class="policy-section">
				<h2>Emergency or Crisis Situations</h2>
				<p>If you are facing financial crisis, debt overwhelm, or mental health challenges related to financial stress:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Seek immediate help from appropriate professionals or hotlines</li>
					<li>Do not rely on general website content for crisis intervention</li>
					<li>Contact licensed counselors, therapists, or financial counselors who can provide personalized support</li>
				</ul>
				<p>MoneyJuan content is not a substitute for professional crisis intervention.</p>
			</section>

			<section class="policy-section">
				<h2>Changes to This Disclaimer</h2>
				<p>
					We may update this Financial Disclaimer as needed. Changes will be posted with a revised date. Your continued use of MoneyJuan after changes indicates acceptance of the updated disclaimer.
				</p>
			</section>

			<section class="policy-section">
				<h2>Acknowledgment</h2>
				<p>By using MoneyJuan, you acknowledge that:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>You have read and understood this Financial Disclaimer</li>
					<li>You will not rely solely on our content for financial decisions</li>
					<li>You will verify information and consult professionals as needed</li>
					<li>You accept full responsibility for your financial decisions</li>
					<li>You understand the limitations of general educational content</li>
				</ul>
			</section>

			<section class="policy-section">
				<h2>Questions</h2>
				<p>
					Questions about this Financial Disclaimer? Contact us at <a href="mailto:contact@moneyjuan.com">contact@moneyjuan.com</a>.
				</p>
			</section>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>

<style>
	.page-content {
		padding: var(--space-lg) var(--space-sm);
		max-width: 860px;
	}

	.page-title {
		text-align: center;
		margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
	}

	.last-updated {
		text-align: center;
		color: var(--color-text-muted);
		margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
	}

	.content-wrapper {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: var(--space-md);
	}

	.policy-section h2 {
		font-size: clamp(1.35rem, 2.7vw, 1.75rem);
		margin-bottom: var(--space-xs);
	}

	.policy-section p {
		font-size: 1.02rem;
		line-height: 1.72;
		color: var(--color-text-muted);
		margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
	}

	.policy-section ul {
		padding-left: 1.2rem;
		margin-bottom: var(--space-sm);
	}

	.policy-section li {
		margin-bottom: 0.45rem;
		color: var(--color-text-muted);
		line-height: 1.65;
	}

	.policy-section a {
		color: var(--color-primary);
		text-decoration: underline;
		text-underline-offset: 2px;
	}

	.policy-section p:last-child,
	.policy-section ul:last-child {
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}

	@media (max-width: 600px) {
		.page-content {
			padding: var(--space-md) var(--space-sm);
		}

		.page-title {
			margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
		}

		.last-updated {
			margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
		}

		.policy-section p,
		.policy-section li {
			font-size: 0.98rem;
		}
	}
</style>
